######### EKS Creation using eksctl command with the lowest cost possible ###########

eksctl create cluster \
  --name test-cluster \
  --region us-east-1 \
  --node-type t2.medium \
  --nodes 1 \
  --nodes-min 1 \
  --nodes-max 2 \
  --nodegroup-name workers

Here a cluster will be created with the name,,,all the things here are changeable after cluster creation ,,but not the k8s cluster name. 
